                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00/1371: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-09T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 9, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. A telegram of May 8 from the American Embassy at Berlin<note n="33"
                        xml:id="d30fn33">Not printed.</note> reads in part as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“German sources indicate that the proclamation of the German-Italian
                            military alliance as well as the reported conversations with Russia are
                            maneuvers intended to frighten the Western Powers and to influence Japan
                            to join Italy and Germany in a military alliance.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
